Package interfaces

Interface BinaryPredicate<T>

All Superinterfaces:
BiPredicate<T,​T>
All Known Subinterfaces:
BinaryPredicate.ArrEquals<T>, BinaryPredicate.Unary<T>
Functional Interface:
This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.
@FunctionalInterface public interface BinaryPredicate<T> extends BiPredicate<T,​T>
Interface that takes 2 values of the same type and returns a boolean value. Useful for Objects.equals(Object, Object) type of tests.
See Also:
test(Object, Object)

  • Method Details

    • test

      boolean test​(T next, T prev)
      For consistency's sake the first parameter 'next' should receive the new/next instance that will enter the test, while the param 'prev' the oldest/previous instance.

      This allows the 'fluid' execution of Object.equals(Object) / Object::equals where the first... being 'next' has a lower probability of being null while the second 'prev' will always be null on first usage. preventing a NullPointerException.

      Specified by:
      test in interface BiPredicate<T,​T>
